So I have learned about their sports culture, with football being the most popular out of the all of them. "Sports offspringing in the Danelaw onslot football, cricket, many styles of rookby, tennis, boxing, badminton, rounders, hocky, billiard, darts, table tennis, bowls, netball, horseracing, houndracing and foxhunting," so seems like they are generally those kind of sports that most Europeans gravitate towards to in terms of demographics. I wonder if they have any motorsports or something to that effect.

Overall, like applying to all of their Factbooks, I do love the generous usage of their own language peppered throughout, though I would be lying if I didn't admit that I have a bit of a difficult time reading as an outsider because some terms are more obscure than others and the meanings and practicality was lost. It's unique, I'll give it that, but it''s "Awesome but impractical," even with the Wordbook.
